process.name: auditJobWorkflow

flowable:field.name: message
flowable:field.flowable:expression: ${flw.format.formatString('Failed to retrieve check results for %s, reason: %s',item, errorDetails == null ? 'Unknown' : errorDetails)}

serviceTask.name: LoadJobProperties
serviceTask.documentation: This node will load the job properties and put the data in the processInstance (execution) variables map.

serviceTask.name: Pre-execution Policy Check
serviceTask.documentation: Retrieves checkset list from policies with the given IDs

serviceTask.name: Loading Operational Data
serviceTask.documentation: Operational data processing prechecks. This task stores the job information into the ETL datastore. The task is gated by the ETL service, that is, the job information store must complete before the job results can be stored.

sequenceFlow.name: false
sequenceFlow.documentation: This is a sequence flow that uses the value of the processInstance variable 'syncExceptions'. It is called from the exclusiveGateway called 'SyncExceptions?'. This sequence flow is the branch taken if the value of process instance variable 'synceExceptions' is Boolean.FALSE. Access the value of the processinstance variable using the UEL syntax '${syncExceptions}'. UEL stands for 'Unified Expression Language'.

sequenceFlow.name: true
sequenceFlow.documentation: This is a sequence flow that uses the value of the processInstance variable 'syncExceptions'. It is called from the exclusiveGateway called 'SyncExceptions?'. This sequence flow is the branch taken if the value of process instance variable 'synceExceptions' is Boolean.TRUE. Access the value of the processinstance variable using the UEL syntax '${syncExceptions}'. UEL stands for 'Unified Expression Language'.
